<div class="heading resPageHeading">


























<h1 >President's Blue and Gold Award of Excellence</h1></div>

<div class="content stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="550f1378-4f11-4889-bf28-b99e21bde87e" >

    <p>The President’s Blue and Gold Award of Excellence recognizes individuals and cross-functional teams in the administration of the university, who have demonstrated excellence in providing services, participating in or leading teams, and demonstrating the Ryerson values to achieve sustained and outstanding results that have significantly advanced the university’s mission. Individual recipients’ scope of influence and responsibility may be at the departmental and/or university-wide level.</p> 
<p>Individual recipients receive a certificate and a one-time monetary award of $5,000 (subject to applicable deductions). Team recipients (a group of two to ten individuals) receive individual certificates and a total one-time monetary award of $7,000 (subject to applicable deductions) to be shared equally among members.</p> 
<p><strong>Key criteria: Innovation; operational excellence; people first</strong></p>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#550f1378-4f11-4889-bf28-b99e21bde87e");});</script></div>

				

				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="95c040b8-f733-4fdf-b0b6-3bf8f3922969" >

    <h2>Nomination guidelines</h2>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#95c040b8-f733-4fdf-b0b6-3bf8f3922969");});</script></div>

				

				
				<div class="resAccordion section">
























 


<div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12">
        <div class="panel-group accordion background-hidden" id="0ceb93dd-309e-4174-8fef-eed8b3b98403" role="tablist" aria-multiselectable="true">
			
				<div class="resAccordionControl" role="group" aria-label="Accordion Actions">
					<button class="resAccordionOpenAll">Open All</button> <button class="resAccordionCloseAll">Close All</button>
				</div>
				<script type="text/javascript">$(document).ready(function(){ initResAccordionControl("0ceb93dd-309e-4174-8fef-eed8b3b98403", false); });</script>
			
            
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <!-- Accordion Heading -->
                <div class="panel-heading container-clipboard">
                    <h3 class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1568399376026-eligibility-and-obligations" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#" href="#accordion-content-1568399376026-eligibility-and-obligations" aria-controls="accordion-content-1568399376026-eligibility-and-obligations" aria-expanded="false">
                            Eligibility and obligations
                        </a>
                    </h3>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1568399376026-eligibility-and-obligations" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1568399376026-eligibility-and-obligations">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1568399376026 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="f8d6f1e7-e60d-43a9-94df-23841926f2ac" >

    <ul> 
 <li>Staff employees (i.e. Senior Administrator or Director, MAC, CUPE 233 or OPSEU) with at least two years of service as of the nomination deadline, employed on a career or term basis.&nbsp;</li> 
 <li>RFA members and associate members are only eligible as part of a team.</li> 
 <li>Individuals can only be nominated for one individual award per year; however the Selection Committee may choose to reassign a nomination to a different award category, based on best fit with the criteria. </li> 
 <li>Nominations are only valid for the year in which they are submitted and must be based on achievements within the past academic year.</li> 
 <li>Employees who receive this award may not receive the same award for the following two academic years (e.g. 2019-2020 recipients cannot receive the same award until 2022-2023. They are ineligible for 2020-2021 and 2021-2022).</li> 
</ul> 
<h4><strong>Team nominations:</strong></h4> 
<ul> 
 <li>Teams can be comprised of up to a maximum of ten individuals.</li> 
 <li>A nominated team member is defined as someone who has made a significant contribution toward a project or initiative. Preference will be given to project-based and/or cross-disciplinary teams.</li> 
 <li>Submit the nomination under the team lead's name. If there is no team lead, select one team member's name.</li> 
</ul>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#f8d6f1e7-e60d-43a9-94df-23841926f2ac");});</script></div>

				</div>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <!-- Accordion Heading -->
                <div class="panel-heading container-clipboard">
                    <h3 class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1568399382935-who-can-submit-a-nomination-" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#" href="#accordion-content-1568399382935-who-can-submit-a-nomination-" aria-controls="accordion-content-1568399382935-who-can-submit-a-nomination-" aria-expanded="false">
                            Who can submit a nomination?
                        </a>
                    </h3>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1568399382935-who-can-submit-a-nomination-" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1568399382935-who-can-submit-a-nomination-">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
